VIATICAL ADMINISTRATORS, INC., A Colorado Corporation, PlaintiffCounter-Defendant-Appellant, v. BLUE PAPER, INC., A Florida Corporation, et al., Defendants-Cross-Defendants, BankUnited, FSB, a Federal Savings Bank, Defendant-Counter-Claimant-Appellee, 900 Hillsboro Mile, Inc., A Florida not-for-profit corporation, et al., Defendants. No. 08-11333. United States Court of Appeals, Eleventh Circuit. Dec. 12, 2008. John A. Hutchings, Dill, Dill, Carr & Stonbraker, P.C., Denver, CO, Eric C. *905Christu, Elk, Christa & Bakst LLP, West Palm Beach, FL, for Plaintiff-Counter-Defendant-Appellant. Daniel A. Miller, Broad & Cassel, West Palm Beach, FL, Richard L. Lapidus, Miami, FL, for Defendant-Counter-ClaimantAppellee.

Before DUBINA, BLACK and FAY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM:

Because we conclude from the record that the district court correctly determined that BankUnited’s mortgage has priority over Viatical Administrators, Inc.’s equitable liens, we affirm the district court’s judgment.

AFFIRMED.
